sentences: Susan Kay Bogguss (born December 30, 1956) is an American country music singer and songwriter.
She began her career in the 1980s as a solo singer.
In the 1990s, six of her songs were Top 10 hits, three albums were certified gold, and one album received a platinum certification.
Susan Kay Bogguss was born on December 30, 1956, in Aledo, Illinois, United States, the youngest of four born to Barbara "B.J." (née Stewart) and Charles "Bud" Bogguss.
